Text.Value: Because there's nothing to eat. Nothing I want to eat.
I think you're in the best place you could possibly be - safely behind bars.
Quite the deviation from my usual routine, of course. Capture, not lure. I didn't bring them in with sweetrolls or anything.
*Behind the exhaustion, starvation, and fear - recognition stirs in her eyes, and with it - hope.*
Who locked you in here?
Let me get you out of there, and you can find something to eat.
I'm sorry. It's the hunger... It's worse than anything I've ever known... No matter what I do, it just doesn't stop.

EditorData.NodeContext: catches herself, and abruptly switches back to apologetic child

Text.Value: What if I free you? Will that help?
*You know that pain well. She's feeling the same hunger that's plagued you for two hundred years.*
What's wrong with you?
That's... one way of looking at it.
Rats. Great idea. Why didn't I think of that? I'll just find the hundred rats I'd need to even make a dent in this hunger.

EditorData.NodeContext: sarcastic

Text.Value: Never give up hope. Trust me, I know what I'm talking about.
Chessa, focus. Resist the beast inside you. You promised!

EditorData.NodeContext: chastising herself in horror for forgetting about her parents now that the vampiric instinct has taken hold of her

Text.Value: And it's all because of him.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'him' = Astarion

Text.Value: Let me free you.
You'll do nothing of the sort. Astarion's with me.
I never thought you'd end up like this. I'm so sorry.
You - you really mean it.

EditorData.NodeContext: a moment of pause, and shifting from anger to hope

Text.Value: How chivalrous of you. As if I need defending from these children.
It's a prison. There must be plenty of rats for you to eat?
That's not a good thing. That was going to be our way out of this.
It wouldn't solve anything, anyway. Not for your parents, not for you.
Why...?

EditorData.NodeContext: suspicious

Text.Value: You want to free us?
We were supposed to be hunters. We spent our whole lives training, studying... You were the one we were supposed to kill!
I know.

EditorData.NodeContext: sadly, knowingly

Text.Value: Well, I hope your parents come and visit you.
I'll show you thirsty!

EditorData.NodeContext: Italics spoken with psychopathic, vampire fury and hunger.

Text.Value: Are you the kids from the Gur camp?
If Cazador wants them, then Cazador can have them. Let's go.
You RAT! You raised our hopes just to kill them. You're worse than Cazador!
Don't think about it - that life is behind you now.
Even when we managed it, all it did was paralyse us. We tried twice each, just to be sure.
Who made you into spawn?
We promised their parents we'd save them.
You're the children from the monster hunter's camp?
Didn't he tell you? He's the one that kidnapped us. He's the reason we're spawns. I'LL KILL YOU.

EditorData.NodeContext: Talking to player about Astarion. Last line directed at Astarion.

Text.Value: Ah. Ah-hah... yes, now that you mention it, I may have done... that.
I'm HUNGRY.
Perhaps that's why you don't understand. You've never known what it truly means to be free. To be tracking prey in the wild...
*Behind the glowing eyes and pallid skin, you recognise the faces of the children you took from the Gur hunters' camp on Cazador's orders.*
What? You expect me to believe that?
If you're a spawn, then you understand how hard it is to resist Cazador's requests.
How? How is it better?
Amends? You think you can amend this?
What use is it, though? They're lost, ravenous, feral. They'd attack any mortal on sight.
Not that you care.
Better off without you, I'd imagine, given what you've become.
Feeding is not the same as killing. They can come back from the brink.
I wouldn't know would I? I've never been a human.
That's rubbish, and you know it! My parents would never stop hunting you.
And roam free, I shall. Goodbye.
I really forgot about them, felt nothing the moment I handed them over to him.
It hurts, doesn't it? The hunger.
I'm here to kill Cazador. Perhaps once I do, the hunger will be over too.
Might I recommend acquiring a taste for rats? They won't sate your appetite, but they help with the hunger.
Now we're no better than you. Worse. At least you get to roam free.
All right, I'll free you once I have the staff.
Uh huh. Sure, first you kidnap us and then you want to save us. That makes sense.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sarcastic (but not TOO sarcastic)

Text.Value: We thought we'd figured it out at first - we could just stake ourselves with sharp twigs from the gutter and be done with it. But - it's harder than it looks.
Don't look at me like that - Cazador's orders.
Parents? You've seen my parents?

EditorData.NodeContext: sad, coming back to herself, remembering a lost life

Text.Value: Good point. There's no reason to free you. It's safer for everyone if you stay right where you are.
You're stronger.
And now I'm here to make amends.
What isn't you?
This doesn't feel good. I don't like this.
Are you feeling all right?
The world will be a safer place with you behind bars.
You're a monster. The worst kind. And you need to leave.
Why are you so hungry?
Deep down somewhere, they're just kids who need our help.
I don't like it any more than you do... but I'm hungry. Starved.
I'm going to help you. How do I free you?
Well that could have gone better.
Leave.
That's... true. The books said so. 'The spawn are only bound so long as their lord lives.'
I'm here to free you. Not kill you.
I'm not a child. I'm EVIL. I'm an evil monster!

EditorData.NodeContext: A child trying to convince us she's really bad.

Text.Value: I can't bear to see you suffering like this because of something I did.
Oh Gods, it can't be...

EditorData.NodeContext: Seing kids he once kidnapped.

Text.Value: It won't make a difference. You're already dead.
What happened to you?
As long as we're here, as long as Cazador's alive, we're - stuck.
Your parents aren't coming. But I am. I'm here to save you.
If you're Cazador's spawn, I'll let him do with you as he wishes.
I don't think I'll ever be able to go home. Not like this.

EditorData.NodeContext: sad, defeated

Text.Value: You're not honestly asking me to sacrifice them, are you?
We need to get these children out of here.
As if you care.
But yours... is off-limits! Off-limits, Chessa!

EditorData.NodeContext: 'But yours...' referring to player's blood with hunger, before catching herself and chastising herself again for slipping into animalistic vampire instincts

Text.Value: If releasing a pack of ravenous, juvenile vampire spawn into the world is the outcome you're after.
They'll be fine, so long as we free you from this place.
All right, I'll free you once I have the staff.
You. You're adorable.
Except you. Chessa, STOP. I'm sorry.

EditorData.NodeContext: hungrily, giving into monstrous vampiric instincts, then catching herself and pulling back

Text.Value: Hey, come back! Don't leave us here!
Let me guess, Cazador?
Hey, you! It's you isn't it? I remember that stupid hair.
Then what are we supposed to do?
Of course I deserve it, but the countless others they'd feed from...
You're making excuses. You just want to bury your sins.
Are you feeling all right?
*This is no ordinary hunger. This is the hunger of a vampire spawn. One that hasn't fed since it was created.*
If we eliminate Cazador, will they be free?
I need to find the key to your cell first. Do you know where it is?
What are you doing? They're going to tear me to shreds... They'd never forgive me for what I've done.
I don't know what you mean. I've never seen these children in my life.
Perhaps you're right.
If I ever get out of here, you'll wish you'd DIED when you were bitten!
The Gur camp, the Gur camp... Maybe? Yes. I think so.

EditorData.NodeContext: The Gur camp is precisely where they're from, but they've half-forgotten now that they're vampire spawn. She's thinking about it, and it stirs a memory, but it's foggy.

Text.Value: So what are you waiting for? Let us out!
Yes... yes I suppose so.
His servant kidnapped us. The pretty one with the frilly clothes and white hair. One moment we're at camp. Then, the world goes dark.
Self-preservation - that actually makes sense. If you'd said anything else, I'd have struggled to believe you.
The next thing I remember, there's someone breathing on my neck, a tongue, and then the pain...
I hope Cazador finds you and drains you to a husk.
I suppose there's a good chance they will.
You want sympathy because you can't hunt me like your parents did?
I'll drink you dry as a desert.

EditorData.NodeContext: Abrupt, frightening switch to a calm, cool, psychopathic vampiric instinct. Genuine evil.

Text.Value: Perhaps if Cazador's dead, you'll be truly free.
Good luck. If you fail, well - I suppose we'll be seeing you again in here.
Please. Whatever you can do.
You know him? Then you understand...
Maybe I am. Maybe that's what I have to do.
You - you're not kidding. Huh.
Hey. Hey you - come closer...
What? What are you looking at?
Leave us alone! You've said enough.
Leave us alone! You've done enough, freak.
Well, what else would you have me do?
Please, if you've any mercy, put us down like the prey we are.
Leave us alone, you monster!
I hope they don't. I hope they stay well away from here.
They're looking for you.
Did you not hear me? We're vampire spawn. And we're hungry. We'll be a risk to everything and everyone we meet!
I can't promise anything, but I'll try.
Isn't it wonderful? A vast improvement.
Smells fresh. Smells alive. Smells like... NO. Chessa, stop it. This isn't you!

EditorData.NodeContext: Getting hungry, italics spoken like a psychopath succumbing to vampiric hunger. Then suddenly realising what they're saying, pulling back and mortified with themselves.

Text.Value: You? It can't be...
I'm sorry it had to end this way. Good luck to you.
You could have just left us here to starve, you know. You didn't have to come and insult us. Arsehole.
You should go. Leave us here. We shouldn't be out there. We'd hurt our families.

EditorData.NodeContext: sad, defeated, given up

Text.Value: I couldn't have put it less delicately if I'd tried.
Have you ever tried eating a rat? Stale as mouldy bread, their blood.
Never give up hope. Trust me, I know what I'm talking about.
Please. Go away now. You're making the hunger worse.
Oh he most certainly will.
Cool it. I'll help you. But you need to tell us how to free you.
I'll kill you! Once I get out of here I'LL KILL YOU!

EditorData.NodeContext: with inhuman rage

Text.Value: You're the one that did this to us. You're the one that took us, and offered us up to be Cazador's spawns.
All these people were ruined because of me. Long ago...
Back away slowly.
I'll take my chances. How do I release you?
I'm not going to let Cazador take advantage of you like he took advantage of me.
It's your fault. You did this to us.

EditorData.NodeContext: with hatred of Astarion

Text.Value: Enough to break your heart.
But still not strong enough to get out of this place. Or away from Cazador.
I'm here to free you.
*Snarl!*
I'm actually here to free you.
You are definitely exactly where you belong. Safely locked away from the rest of us.
It's Cazador.

EditorData.NodeContext: horrified by her own monstrosity

Text.Value: I was in the prime of my life when I was turned.
Because you're vampire spawn. You should be out in the world feasting, not locked in a dungeon!
I'm not going to kill you. I'm going to free you.
It's that obvious, is it? Urgh. Then there's no hope for us, even if we got out of here.

EditorData.NodeContext: dejected, whatever sliver of denial she was hanging onto is now gone

Text.Value: I wish I could see my father again.
This hunger... I'm starving.
I just... I never want to see these little scraps of misery again. The world doesn't need to know my shame.
I'm hungry. Starved.
They miss you. Probably.
I regret it. I regret everything.
It is you. I knew it!
We're not children! Don't call us children! We'll drink you dry.

EditorData.NodeContext: Italics spoken with psychopathic, vampire fury and hunger.

Text.Value: Changed my mind. Maybe you should wait here until your parents arrive.
LIAR! You're the one who kidnapped us! You're the reason we're spawns! I'LL KILL YOU.
That's true...
You'll never die.
I miss them. I think. Or perhaps it's the hunger... oh I don't know. It's so hard to tell!

EditorData.NodeContext: sentimental, but also confused, frustrated

Text.Value: NO! No... you can't. You mustn't.
Thirsty little brats, aren't they?
Well, keep trying.
You can tell them yourself when I free you.
Tell them... tell them you couldn't find us.

EditorData.NodeContext: First line, trying to think of something nice to say. Second line, realising that's the only nice thing you could possibly say to save her parents from pain.

Text.Value: NO! Please - you can't. Not like this. Our families can't see what we've become. What Cazador turned us into.
Cazador.
My parents... I wonder how they're doing...
And you look a tasty treat... No, Chessa, NO. Gods, if I could only think, but this hunger...

EditorData.NodeContext: psychopathically cold, succumbing for a moment to vampiric instincts

Text.Value: I'm sorry. It's the hunger... If you were to free us... there's no knowing what we'll do.
I don't like the way you're talking about me.
I hope you know what you're doing. Have you ever disappointed a child before?
But did you have to kidnap us?
Better off without you, now that I've seen what you've become.
Everything was taken from me, too.
Quit whining. You're a vampire spawn now. That's much better than being human.
All the monsters I ever met were in books. I never even made it to the adult hunt. But now I'm one of them. I'm a spawn.

EditorData.NodeContext: on the verge of tears as they're reminiscing and realising what they've become

Text.Value: Simple. I save your lives, your parents stop hunting me.
I hope he finds you and drains you to a husk.

EditorData.NodeContext: Italics spoken with psychopathic, vampire fury and hunger.

Text.Value: I've changed my mind. I think it's safer you stay right where you are.
You better watch out, our parents will be here soon. And when they find you, they'll - urgh.
Camp... monster hunters... the Gur camp? Oh gods - my parents' camp!
I'll free you once I have Cazador's staff.
Now please leave. You're making me hungry.
Astarion, why do these children know you?
Thanks. Arsehole.

EditorData.NodeContext: sarcastic

Text.Value: I'm not about to kill a child.
Cazador's got this staff - it controls the doors. If you get it, you can set everyone free. If you get it... somehow...
Maybe you'd deserve it.

Synopsis: Dialog with a child in Cazador's Dungeon. She's the daughter of a monster hunter you likely met before in the game. She's been turned into a vampire spawn, the kind of monster her family would normally hunt, and knows exactly how bad that is.
